    "More moderately, instead of an optimal, we can assume that there is a justified threshold for moral permissibility on the basis of some notion of moral value.",
    "For instance,Parfit (2011) argues that it is erroneous to believe that there are profound disagreements between consequentialists, contractualists, and Kantians, writing: \"these people are climbing the same mountain on different sides\" (p. 385)."
